The paper deals with algorithms for computing shortest paths among obstacles in the plane, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of bicriteria paths and the consideration of one-point and two-point queries suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the fields of optimization (cs.DS, cs.DM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.SI).
